cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SI

This paper deals with the problem of learning the structure of Bayesian networks from observational data, which is a fundamental problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a polynomial-time algorithm for learning sparse Gaussian Bayesian networks, which is a specific type of Bayesian network. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) the most likely category. The paper also deals with high-dimensional settings, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses information-theoretic limits, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper compares its method to existing state-of-the-art methods, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
